June 15

Siloso Beach

NUS

biggest beach event

SunNUS 2019 is back and bigger than ever before! Jam-packed with a variety of sporting activities including team sports, a race around Sentosa island, and a pageant and carnival games happening by Siloso beach, there's something at SunNUS for everyone!

​

Join us this June 15 at Siloso beach for NUS's most anticipated beach event and a day of fun under the sun! We'll see you there!

Introducing to you one of the biggest activites in SunNUS, the Team Sports Series! With 5 different sports to choose from - Frisbee, Volleyball, Touch Rugby, Tchoukball and Captain's Ball, team up with your friends and challenge other teams! We also have non-competitive sports - Frisbee and Volleyball for those who want to pick up a new sport. So come join us on for an exciting day at Siloso beach!

Craving an adventure? SunNUS' signature Mount Imbiah challenge is back BIGGER and BETTER than before! With our 5km run and first-ever 10km cycling component, explore the undiscovered secrets of Sentosa and test your fortitude! Only the strong in mind and spirit will prevail. Do you think you have what it takes to conquer our challenge? If you do then what are you waiting for? Sign up now!

    function doScrolling(element, duration) { var startingY = window.pageYOffset var elementY = getElementY(element) // If element is close to page's bottom then window will scroll only to some position above the element. var targetY = document.body.scrollHeight - elementY < window.innerHeight ? document.body.scrollHeight - window.innerHeight : elementY var diff = targetY - startingY // Easing function: easeInOutCubic // From: https://gist.github.com/gre/1650294 var easing = function (t) { return t<.5 ? 4*t*t*t : (t-1)*(2*t-2)*(2*t-2)+1 } var start if (!diff) return // Bootstrap our animation - it will get called right before next frame shall be rendered. window.requestAnimationFrame(function step(timestamp) { if (!start) start = timestamp // Elapsed miliseconds since start of scrolling. var time = timestamp - start // Get percent of completion in range [0, 1]. var percent = Math.min(time / duration, 1) // Apply the easing. // It can cause bad-looking slow frames in browser performance tool, so be careful. percent = easing(percent) window.scrollTo(0, startingY + diff * percent) // Proceed with animation as long as we wanted it to. if (time < duration) { window.requestAnimationFrame(step) } }) } document.getElementById('comp-jtr30pz90').addEventListener('click', doScrolling.bind(null, '#comp-jtu7cquwbalata', 1200)) document.getElementById('comp-jtr30pz91').addEventListener('click', doScrolling.bind(null, '#comp-jtu4ipvxlink', 1200)) document.getElementById('comp-jtr30pz92').addEventListener('click', doScrolling.bind(null, '#comp-jtu4lc0nlink', 1200)) document.getElementById('comp-jtr30pz93').addEventListener('click', doScrolling.bind(null, '#comp-jtu4pysnlink', 1200)) document.getElementById('comp-jtr30pz94').addEventListener('click', doScrolling.bind(null, '#comp-juc4d2joinlineContent', 1200)) document.getElementById('comp-jtr30pz95').addEventListener('click', doScrolling.bind(null, '#comp-jtr5tiehinlineContent', 1200)) document.getElementById('comp-jtr30pz96').addEventListener('click', doScrolling.bind(null, '#comp-jucgnvcbinlineContent', 1200))
